snippet: Egypt’s new military-led government is increasing pressure on supporters of ousted President Mohamed Morsi to back down from their public protests.
abstract: Egypt's new military-led government says it is freezing assets of 14 Islamist allies of ousted Pres Mohamed Morsi, stepping up pressure on his supporters to back down from their continuing public protests demanding his release and reinstatement.
lead_paragraph: Egypt’s new military-led government is increasing pressure on supporters of ousted President Mohamed Morsi to back down from their public protests.
